public class RepBasedExerciseEntry extends ExerciseEntry
Represents an exercise entry that is based on repetitions and sets.

A RepBasedExerciseEntry specifies the number of sets, repetitions per set, and the average duration per repetition. This class extends ExerciseEntry and calculates calories burned using the MET value of the sport, the userâ€™s weight, and the total exercise duration (sets x reps x average duration per repetition).

    • calculateCalories

      public double calculateCalories()
      Calculates the calories burned for this entry.

      The calculation is based on the total duration (in hours), the user's weight, and the MET value of the sport.

      A negative value is returned to represent calorie burning (so that net calorie calculations can subtract exercise calories directly).

      Specified by:
      calculateCalories in class Entry
      Returns:
      the negative number of calories burned
